Qwaqwa taps still run dry following further delays of promised water tanks. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - QwaQwa residents have once again been left high and dry. Government has failed to deliver 5,000 water tanks as promised. READ: CT, Joburg warn water supply in jeopardy amid power cuts It only sent five water trucks to help deal with the drought. Residents are demanding supply directly to their homes.